Sentencas: This paper presents electrochemical impedance simulation of a solid oxide fuel cell anode.
Titulo: A comprehensive simulation of gas concentration impedance for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: The model takes in to account the gas-phase transport processes both in the gas channel and within the porous electrode and couples the gas transport processes with the electrochemical kinetics.
Titulo: A comprehensive simulation of gas concentration impedance for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: The gas phase mass transport is modeled using the transient conservation equations (mass, momentum and species equations) and Butler-Volmer equation is used for the anode electrochemistry.
Titulo: A comprehensive simulation of gas concentration impedance for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: In order to solve the system of non linear equations, an in-house code based on the finite volume method is developed and utilized.
Titulo: A comprehensive simulation of gas concentration impedance for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: Results show a depressed semicircle in the Nyquist plot, which originates from gas transport processes in the gas channel, in addition to a Warburg diffusion impedance originates from gas transport in the thick porous anode.
Titulo: A comprehensive simulation of gas concentration impedance for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: The simulation results are in good agreement with published experimental data.
Titulo: A comprehensive simulation of gas concentration impedance for solid oxide fuel cell anodes
